sort:
-> cat <file_name> | sort
* will sort all the lines in file ,in alphabertical order
-> this type of sorting used is lexicographic:
* which is ASCII character sorting
* so bear in mind that upper cases before lower cases
-> sort also has the "man sort" which shows options 

-> after sorting you can cut lines to display names only,if it was names,surnames and numbers.
* cat <file_name> |sort|cut -d ,-f 1 | sed "s(meaning substitute)/thabo/Thabo/"
* sed section will change thabo to Thabo.
* tr "t" "T" changes characters in words takes two commands 
e.g 
thabos 
tshepos
tr "ts" "TS"
ThaboS
TShepoS

